The White House Office of the Press Secretary held a press briefing with U.S. Ambassador to NATO Ivo Daalder and Deputy National Security Advisor for Strategic Communications Ben Rhodes. They discussed the NATO Strategic Concept and the alliance's position for the 21st century. They highlighted the progress made in resolving important issues, such as missile defense and the reset with Russia. They also discussed the decision to build a NATO missile defense system and the invitation for Russia to cooperate on missile defense. The briefing also touched on the alliance's approach to Afghanistan and the transition to Afghan lead responsibility. They emphasized the importance of the New START treaty and its impact on European security. The briefing concluded by addressing the role of nuclear weapons in the alliance and the credibility of the President's agenda.